io.tarantool.driver

Class ProxyTarantoolClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.tarantool.driver.ProxyTarantoolClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TarantoolCallOperations, TarantoolClient, TarantoolEvalOperations, ProxyOperationsMapping, AutoCloseable

    public class ProxyTarantoolClient
extends Object
implements TarantoolClient, ProxyOperationsMapping
    Client implementation that decorates a TarantoolClient instance, proxying all CRUD operations through the instance's call method to the proxy functions defined on the Tarantool instance(s). Proxy functions to be called can be specified by overriding the methods of the implemented ProxyOperationsMapping interface. These functions must be public API functions available on the Tarantool instance fro the connected API user. It is recommended to use this client with the CRUD module ( https://github.com/tarantool/crud) installed on the target Tarantool instance. See https://github.com/tarantool/examples/blob/master/profile-storage/README.md
